Diagnostic characters. Male: lateral vitta with anterior mark extending medially, so that a transverse stripe is present across scutum; pigmentation on postnotum restricted to dorsum; pigmentation on T II extending from anterior to posterior margins (
Borkent, 1984
). Female: thorax with a dark dorsolateral stripe, covering the posterior half of the medial vitta and anterior half of the lateral vitta ; post-genital plate truncated at apex. Pupa: pedes spurii B present on T II; S II with 3 L setae and S III–IV with 4 L setae.
